  "prompt": "Is the body of the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) still untouched in his tomb in Madinah? Has anyone ever seen the body since his burial in 632?",
  "response": "Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) was buried in his tomb in Madinah in 632 AD, and his grave is located in Al-Masjid an-Nabawi (the Prophet's Mosque). The sanctuary is highly revered by Muslims and is a popular pilgrimage site.\n\nAccording to Islamic tradition and historical accounts, there is no credible evidence or authenticated report indicating that the body of Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) has ever been exhumed or seen since his burial. The grave is considered sacred, and there are strict prohibitions against tampering with or disturbing it.\n\nMoreover, tampering with graves in general, especially those of revered figures, is considered highly disrespectful and is strictly forbidden in Islam. Therefore, the body of Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) remains untouched, and there have been no known instances of the grave being disturbed since his burial.",
